(x,y)
 X = x+y \\ Y = 2x-y  
 x=(X+Y)/3 \\ y=(2X-Y)/3 
 y = 5 x + 1 
 (2X-Y)/3 = 5 (X+Y)/3+1 \Rightarrow Y = -1/2 X - 1/2
\begin{pmatrix} X \\ Y \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 1 \\ 2 & -1\end{pmatrix} \, \begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \end{pmatrix} 
\begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 1 \\ 2 & -1\end{pmatrix} ^{-1} \, \begin{pmatrix} X \\ Y \end{pmatrix} 
r
\theta
 r = \sqrt{x^2+y^2} \\ \theta = \arctan2(x,y) 
